# Auckland Grammar School Site Act 1911Local Act1911 No 18

Date of assent21 October 1911

## Contents

[Title][0]
    
*   [Preamble][1]

[1][2] [Short Title][2]

[2][3] [Land vested in Auckland Grammar School Board][3]

[3][4] [Board to erect buildings for secondary school][4]

[Schedule][5]  
[][5]

---

An Act to transfer certain Land in the City of Auckland, being Part of the Auckland Gaol Reserve, to the Auckland Grammar School Board as a Site for a Secondary School.
    
*   #### Preamble
    
    WHEREAS the land described in the Schedule hereto is part of the Auckland Gaol Reserve, but is no longer required therefor: And whereas it is desired to transfer the said land to the Auckland Grammar School Board as a site for a secondary school on the terms and conditions hereinafter appearing:

BE IT THEREFORE ENACTED by the General Assembly of New Zealand in Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:---

##### 1 Short Title
    
*   This Act may be cited as The Auckland Grammar School Site Act 1911\.

##### 2 Land vested in Auckland Grammar School Board
    
*   The land described in the Schedule hereto is hereby vested in the Auckland Grammar School Board in trust as a site for a secondary school, subject to the provisions of this Act.

##### 3 Board to erect buildings for secondary school
    
*   (1) The said Board shall cause to be erected on the said land buildings suitable and necessary for the purposes of such school, to the satisfaction of the Minister of Education.
    
    (2) No building shall be erected on the said land except according to plans and in a manner approved by the said Minister.
    
    (3) Unless within ten years from the passing of this Act the said Board has erected buildings as aforesaid, the Governor may by Proclamation resume possession of such land, and the land shall, as from the date of that Proclamation, revert to the Crown.

---

## Schedule
    
*   The description contained in this Schedule was substituted, as from 7 November 1912, by section [3][6] Reserves and other Lands Disposal and Public Bodies Empowering Act 1912 (1912 No 46).
*   The description contained in this Schedule was further substituted, as from 10 December 1918, by section [9(3)][7] Reserves and other Lands Disposal and Public Bodies Empowering Act 1918 (1918 No 23).

All that area in the Auckland Land District, containing by admeasurement seventeen acres three roods and six decimal seventy-four perches, more or less, being parts of Allotments 105, 106, 107, and 108 of Section 6, Suburbs of Auckland: bounded towards the north-east by Reeve's Road, 808.2 links; towards the east generally by Firth's Road to its junction with Mountain Road; thence by Mountain Road for a distance of 345.77 links; thence towards the south-west by lines bearing 313° 54′ distance 461.6 links, bearing 291° 46′ distance 505.75 links; thence towards the west and north-west generally by lines bearing 160° 4′ distance 616.38 links, bearing 352° 6′ distance 77.58 links, bearing 73° 22′ 39″ distance 104.2 links, bearing 73° 2′ 22″ distance 560.03 links, bearing 36° 42′ distance 614.9 links, bearing 10° 46′ distance 207.4 links, bearing 284° 1′ distance 97.4 links, bearing 3° 43′ 30″ distance 610.2 links, to the point of commencement on Reeve's Road: as the same is delineated on a plan deposited in the Head Office of the Lands and Survey Department, at Wellington, and numbered 1780\.

